.some()   -> Checks if at least one element satisfies the condition.
             Returns a boolean (true/false) without returning the element itself.

.find()   -> Finds the first element that matches the condition.
             Returns the element object (or undefined if none found).

.filter() -> Finds all elements that match the condition.
             Returns an array of matching elements (can be empty).

.map()    -> Transforms each element of an array into a new array.
             Returns a new array with the transformed values.

callback() -> A function passed as an argument to another function.
              It can take parameters, run inside the main function,
              and update dynamically depending on input.

forEach() → Iterates over each element of an array and executes a 
            given callback function for each element.